{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Add Height and Weight to The Equality Act 2010",
        "additional_details": "Scientific findings: \r\n- \"employers prefer not to hire or promote short employees, and that they do not adequately compensate them\" https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3166828\r\n- \"weight discrimination by individuals with obesity were common, and its negative consequences are highly relevant issues within society\" https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26596238/\r\n\r\nThe law is meant to protect us all. Why doesn't it cover all types of  discrimination? This is wrong. Amend the Equality Act.",
        "background": "Height and weight discrimination is a proven, yet largely unrecognised bias in society. Several scientific studies have reported this, with one study stating in some cases weight/height \"were even more prevalent than discrimination due to gender and race\". https://www.nature.com/articles/ijo200822",
